title: Mohammad Nabi century helps Afghanistan level ODI series against Zimbabwe
text:
Mohammad Nabi century helps Afghanistan level ODI series against Zimbabwe 18 Oct 2015 15:31:56 
comments 
Afghanistan cruised to a 58-run win in the second one-day international against Zimbabwe in Bulawayo to level the five-match series. 
Mohammad Nabi's 116 off 121 deliveries and Noor Ali Zadran's 60 allowed the tourists to post 271 for five having elected to bat. 
Aftab Alam, Dawlat Zadran and Samiullah Shenwari claimed two wickets apiece as the home side were dismissed for 213. Related Sport News
